Perfect as a dipping sauce for fried chicken, shrimp or beef burger, sweet chili has a sweet, sour, and Â slightly spicy taste that will wow your taste buds. It subtly enhances the taste of food and the sauce is easy to make and goes very well with fried foods. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Using a blender or food processor, blend the chilli to desired size. Step 2 Using a pan, bring the water, vinegar, salt, sugar, garlic and chilli to a simmer. Step 3 Add cornstarch to the mixture, until the sauce has thickened. Do a taste test and add the desired ingredients. Step 4 Let the sauce cool before storing in the fridge. Step 5 Once cooled, enjoy with your favourite fried food.